Description: include <cstring> in preferences.cpp for GCC 15 / FLTK 1.4.5
 preferences.cpp calls strcpy/strncpy/strcat/strrchr but relied on a
 transitive include that FLTK 1.4.5's headers no longer provide, so the
 build fails with "was not declared in this scope" under GCC 15.
Author: Foundry Linux <packages@foundrylinux.org>
Forwarded: not-yet
Last-Update: 2026-06-10
--- a/src/preferences.cpp
+++ b/src/preferences.cpp
@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
 #pragma warning(push, 0)
+#include <cstring>
 #include <FL/Fl_Preferences.H>
 #include <FL/filename.H>
 #include <FL/fl_utf8.h>
